{
  "text": "Let us now look at the contribution coming from zero modes. As in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , these arise due to asymptotic symmetries. To understand the dependence on L of this integration, one evaluates the Jacobian from the coefficients of the zero modes, to the parameters labeling the supergroup of asymptotic symmetries. Let us suppose that there is a factor of L \u00b1\u03b2 A for each zero mode. Then, the total contribution to the partition function from the zero modes is L [CITATION_6] and hence to the free energy is",
  "correct_citation": {
